*libmowgli-0.3.1 (10 Aug 2007)

  10 Aug 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.3.0.ebuild,
  +libmowgli-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Version bump to 0.3.1; marked 0.3.0 stable on PPC, PPC64 & X86. Tested on a
  PowerBook 5,9; PowerMac 7,3 & Centrino laptop respectively.

  13 Jul 2007; Steve Dibb <beandog@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.1.5.ebuild:
  amd64 stable

*libmowgli-0.3.0 (09 Jul 2007)

  09 Jul 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +libmowgli-0.3.0.ebuild:
  New upstream release that uses dancing trees for faster dictionary searches.

  04 Jul 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.1.4.ebuild,
  libmowgli-0.1.5.ebuild, libmowgli-0.2.0.ebuild:
  The atheme domain has moved, update ebuilds accordingly.

*libmowgli-0.2.0 (29 May 2007)

  29 May 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.1.5.ebuild,
  +libmowgli-0.2.0.ebuild:
  New upstream release, adds new features such as global storage and spinlock
  handling. Also features updated documentation. Marked 0.1.5 stable on PPC,
  PPC64 & X86. Tested on PowerBook 5,9; PowerMac 7,3 and Pentium M
  respectively.

  16 May 2007; Steve Dibb <beandog@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.1.4.ebuild:
  amd64 stable

*libmowgli-0.1.5 (28 Apr 2007)

  28 Apr 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +libmowgli-0.1.5.ebuild:
  Version bump.

*libmowgli-0.1.4 (11 Apr 2007)

  11 Apr 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> -libmowgli-0.1.3.ebuild,
  +libmowgli-0.1.4.ebuild:
  Version bump. Now comes bundled with examples, and a random number generator
  has been added.

  02 Apr 2007; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.1.3.ebuild:
  Do not attempt to install README & TODO as documentation, these files do not
  exist. As pointed out by Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> in bug #171580.

  02 Apr 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> libmowgli-0.1.3.ebuild:
  Add ~ia64 keyword wrt bug 171580

